article.headline: San Diego 60, Chapman 12
article.story:
SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Josh Johnson threw three touchdown passes and
Adam Hannula set a school record for career touchdown catches to
lead San Diego to a 60-12 win over Chapman on Saturday night.

Johnson hit Hannula with an 8-yard touchdown pass midway through
the third quarter to give the Toreros' a 39-6 lead and move Hannula
into first place on San Diego's all-time list with his 33rd career
TD reception.

San Diego (8-1), which already clinched first place in the
Pioneer Football League's North Division, fell behind early against
its Division III opponents. Chapman (2-6) controlled the ball for
more than nine minutes on the game's opening drive. Chase Twedell
scored on a 13-yard run to cap the 16-play, 80-yard drive for a 6-0
lead,

But the Toreros scored on all four of their first-half
possessions for a 25-6 halftime lead. San Diego got touchdown runs
of 35 yards by Kevin Herron and 5 yards by Jon Polk. Johnson also
hit Nick Garton with a 10-yard scoring pass and Hutch Parker kicked
a 25-yard field goal.

Josh Denton scored twice on runs of 22 and 2 yards for the
Toreros, who out-gained the Panthers 533 yards to 186.

Johnson, who finished 18-for-25 passing for 248 yards in less
than three quarters, also threw a TD pass of 4 yards to Matt
Koller.

Hannula, already San Diego's career leader in catches and
reception yardage, caught six passes for 101 yards.

Max Nikolenko scored on a 2-yard run for Chapman's other score.
